						               													<description>Master of the World, 1812 in Russia, Phase One: The Invasion&amp;#10; The 1812 campaign is arguably Napoleon&amp;rsquo;s most well known campaign and one of the great tragedies of military history. It is also the story of Russia&amp;rsquo;s First Great Patriotic War, repelling a great invader. In excess of 600,000 soldiers and support personnel crossed the Niemen River from the Grand Duchy of Warsaw into Imperial Russia under the French Imperial flag beginning on 24 June, 1812.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Master of the World includes everything you need to begin recreating the first phase of Napoleon's disastrous 1812 Russian campaign: organization, maps, historical briefings, and uniforms. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     One campaign&amp;#10;     Nine scenarios&amp;#10;     Twenty-seven maps&amp;#10;     Over 800 uniform images! &amp;#10;     created especially for inclusion in this series and offering Nearly 200 pages&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10; &amp;#10;Let's start a land war in Asia&amp;hellip;&amp;#10; 9 scenarios covering the French main army's advance to Moscow:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Mir&amp;#10;     Saltanovka &amp;ndash; Two versions: The Spoiler Attack and Clear the Way to Mogilev&amp;#10;     Ostrovno&amp;#10;     Vitebsk&amp;#10;     1st Krasne&amp;#10;     Smolensk &amp;ndash; Two versions: Preserve the Army and Save the Holy City&amp;#10;     Lubino&amp;#10;     Schwardino&amp;#10;     Borodino&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Master of the World Campaign Guide is compatible with Et sans r&amp;eacute;sultat! Original and Second Edition as well as most any other tabletop Napoleonic wargame.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
